President Cyril Ramaphosa announced his new cabinet on Monday evening at the Union Buildings in Pretoria. Ramaphosa thanked the outgoing ministers for their contribution to the country. “I wish to express my appreciation to all outgoing Ministers and Deputy Ministers for their service to government and to the people of South Africa,” said Ramaphosa. Former Police minister Fikile Mbalula took to twitter to wish the new police minister Bheki Cele well. “Good regards to BHEKI Cele I know he will do a good job bopha Ndosi,” said Mbalula. We look at the outgoing ministers and deputies. Ousted Ministers and Deputies: Joe Maswanganye (Former Transport Minister) David Mahlobo (Former Energy Minister) Fikile Mbalula (Former Police Minister) Faith Muthambi (Former Public Service & Admin Minister) Hlengiwe Mkhize (Former Higher Education & Training Minister) Bongani Bongo (Former State Security Minister) Des Van Rooyen (Former COGTA Minister) Mosebenzi Zwane (Former Mineral Resources Minister) Nathi Nhleko (Former Public Works Minister) Lynne Brown (Former Public Enterprises Minister) Tandi Mahambehlala (Former Deputy Minister of Communication) Ben Martins (Former Deputy Minister of Public Enterprises) -TNA Reporter